WEBVTT

00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:03.416
to write a really good piece
about what had happened

00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:05.840
and why he thought
what had happened was wrong.

00:07:06.600 --> 00:07:11.136
The next day there was an editorial
in the "New York Times"

00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:14.456
with the title of
"Heumann v. The Board of Education"

00:07:14.480 --> 00:07:16.776
and the "New York Times"
came out in support

00:07:16.800 --> 00:07:18.896
of my getting my teaching license.

00:07:18.920 --> 00:07:22.816
(Applause)

00:07:22.840 --> 00:07:24.176
And then the same day,

00:07:24.200 --> 00:07:29.056
I got a call from an attorney
who was writing a book about civil rights.

00:07:29.080 --> 00:07:32.376
And he was calling me to interview me,